{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584449","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584449"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:47:22+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:47:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14523"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14523","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14523"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.13,0.03,0.37,0.42,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7218"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64345"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7218","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7218"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14523"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49777"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4899"},{"type":"tags","id":"4900"},{"type":"tags","id":"4914"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"17515"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17516"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64345","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/64345"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe hemiazygos vein is an important venous structure that drains blood from the posterior thoracic wall.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is a tributary of the hemiazygos vein?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Right superior phrenic veins","Pericardial veins","Left superior intercostal vein","Left posterior intercostal veins","Right bronchial veins"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe hemiazygos vein is an important venous structure in the posterior thorax. It plays a crucial role in draining blood from various structures on the left side of the body.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eleft posterior intercostal veins\u003C/strong\u003E are correct tributaries of the hemiazygos vein. The hemiazygos vein is located on the left side of the vertebral column and receives blood from the lower intercostal spaces.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eright superior phrenic veins\u003C/strong\u003E drain into the superior vena cava or brachiocephalic vein. \u003Cstrong\u003EPericardial veins\u003C/strong\u003E typically drain into the azygos vein system but are not tributaries of the hemiazygos vein. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eleft superior intercostal vein\u003C/strong\u003E more commonly empties into the left brachiocephalic vein. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eright bronchial veins\u003C/strong\u003E drain into the azygos vein, not the hemiazygos vein.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The hemiazygos vein receives tributaries from the left side of the body, including the left posterior intercostal veins from the lower thoracic spaces.","The hemiazygos vein is a counterpart to the azygos vein on the left side of the body and drains into the azygos vein at the level of T8 or T9 vertebra."],"references":["Netter, F. H. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: Classic Regional Approach-Ebook. 2022. Elsevier Health Sciences","Shahoud JS, Miao JH, Bolla SR. Anatomy, Thorax, Heart Aorta. [Updated 2023 Jul 24]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538140/Donohue JR, Daly DT. Anatomy, Thorax, Azygos Veins. [Updated 2023 Jul 30]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK554430/"